The paper discusses the application of quantum models in data science, specifically in item recommendation. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the theoretical aspects of quantum models, including their relation to probabilistic models and their efficiency in representing certain datasets, which could fall under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and theoretical computer science (cs.CC). Finally, the paper introduces a method for computing hierarchical orderings of properties of users and items, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
